[[cdo:3 nguŏk 20 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[zh-min-nan:3 goe̍h 20 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[zh-yue:三月廿]] {{Lunisolar March}} '''March 20''' is the 20th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Shōwa|ja|正和|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1312]] {{ill|April 27|ja|4月27日}}) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Ōchō|ja|応長}} to {{ill|Shōwa|ja|正和}}.
== Births == * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1834]] {{ill|April 28|ja|4月28日}}) – {{ill|Maehara Issei|ja|前原一誠}}, a member of the [[Chōshū Domain|長州藩]] (died [[1876]]). * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年}} ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 12|ja|4月12日}}) – {{ill|Akiyama Masayuki|ja|秋山真之}}, a naval military personnel (died [[1918]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Eishō|ja|永承|12=draft}} 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦}} [[1326]] {{ill|April 23|ja|4月23日}}) – {{ill|Kuniyoshi Shinnō|ja|邦良親王}}, the first prince of {{ill|Go-Nijō Tennō|ja|後二条天皇}} and the progenitor of the {{ill|Kidera-no-miya|ja|木寺宮家}} (born [[1300]]). * {{ill|Keichō|ja|慶長|12=draft}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} [[1604]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日}}) – {{ill|Kuroda Takakazu|ja|黒田孝高}}, also known as 【Nyosui】 and 【Kanbei】, a military commander and Christian daimyō (born [[1546]]).
