{{Lunisolar March}} '''March 20''' is the 20th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Shōwa|ja|正和|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1312]] {{ill|April 27|ja|4月27日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Ōchō|ja|応長|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|Shōwa|ja|正和|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. == Births == * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1834]] {{ill|April 28|ja|4月28日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Maehara Issei|ja|前原一誠|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a member of the [[Chōshū Domain|長州藩]] (died [[1876]]). * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 12|ja|4月12日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Akiyama Masayuki|ja|秋山真之|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a naval military personnel (died [[1918]]). == Deaths == * {{ill|Eishō|ja|永承|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1326]] {{ill|April 23|ja|4月23日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Kuniyoshi Shinnō|ja|邦良親王|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the first prince of {{ill|Go-Nijō Tennō|ja|後二条天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and the progenitor of the {{ill|Kidera-no-miya|ja|木寺宮家|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (born [[1300]]). * {{ill|Keichō|ja|慶長|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1604]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Kuroda Takakazu|ja|黒田孝高|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, also known as 【Nyosui】 and 【Kanbei】, a military commander and Christian daimyō (born [[1546]]).
